rnal service or extra required dependency, but its resolved Vert.x Core dependency pulls Netty 4.2.2.Final, which needs explicit unsafe-access system properties for Java 25 native-image runtime tests.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native runtime execution of the generated tests, set system properties `sun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `io.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`, preferably via `nativeTest` runtime arguments. The existing 5.0.0 test already does this for Netty 4.2.x but gates it to version `5.0.0`; 5.0.1 resolves Netty 4.2.2.Final and needs the same treatment. Meaningful coverage can use an in-process Vert.x `HttpServer` on localhost for WebClient requests, JSON bodies, forms/multipart, redirects, sessions, and caching; no Docker service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"OAuth2WebClient/OpenID discovery paths involve the optional `io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2` dependency and potentially an identity-provider flow; avoid those paths for baseline coverage unless intentionally adding and justifying extra setup.\",\n    \"The unsafe-access properties are primarily a Java 24+/25 Netty native-runtime concern; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_029af0e7f2357fce016a3f42adaaf48190960cbc701236a8cd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1172, "output": 796, "cacheRead": 42496, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44464, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782530723907, "responseId": "resp_029af0e7f2357fce016a3f42a4baa8819086bd3f777666aa7d"}}
